SIMPLE: structure
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Structure
<hw>Struc"ture</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>structura</ets>, from <ets>struere</ets>, <ets>structum</ets>, to
arrange, build, construct; perhaps akin to E. <ets>strew</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>structure</ets>. Cf. <er>Construe</er>, <er>Destroy</er>,
<er>Instrument</er>, <er>Obstruct</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of building; the practice of erecting buildings; construction.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His son builds on, and never is content⟦br⟧
Till the last farthing is in <qex>structure</qex> spent.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Dryden, Jr.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Manner of building; form; make;
construction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Want of insight into the <qex>structure</qex> and constitution of
the terraqueous globe.</q> <rj><qau>Woodward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Arrangement of parts, of organs, or of constituent
particles, in a substance or body; <as>as, the <ex>structure</ex> of a
rock or a mineral; the <ex>structure</ex> of a sentence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It [basalt] has often a prismatic <qex>structure</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Dana.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Manner of organization; the
arrangement of the different tissues or parts of animal and vegetable
organisms; <as>as, organic <ex>structure</ex>, or the <ex>structure</ex>
of animals and plants; cellular <ex>structure</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>That which is built; a building; esp., a building of
some size or magnificence; an edifice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>There stands a <qex>structure</qex> of majestic frame.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Columnar structure</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Columnar</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Structured</ent>⟦br⟧
